{"title":"Topeak’s Versamount Allow for Cargo or Bottle Cages on Your Suspension Fork","link":"https://theradavist.com/2021/02/topeaks-versamount-allow-for-cargo-or-bottle-cages-on-your-suspension-fork/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=topeaks-versamount-allow-for-cargo-or-bottle-cages-on-your-suspension-fork","date":1613055603000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><section><article id=\"article-205554\"><div><p><img src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/02/versamount.png?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" alt=\"Topeak’s Versamount Allow for Cargo or Bottle Cages on Your Suspension Fork\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/02/versamount.png?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w,https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/02/versamount.png?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/02/versamount.png?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" data-base-url=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2021/02/versamount.png\" data-base-quality=\"75\" data-alt-srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/02/versamount.png?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w,https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/02/versamount.png?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/02/versamount.png?w=2000&amp;quality=75\"></p></div><header><h4>Radar</h4></header><div><p><img src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/02/versamount.png?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/02/versamount.png?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/02/versamount.png?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/02/versamount.png?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" data-base-url=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/02/versamount.png\" data-base-quality=\"75\" data-alt-srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/02/versamount.png?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/02/versamount.png?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/02/versamount.png?w=2000&amp;quality=75\"></p><p>On <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2021/02/jonah-and-his-kokopelli-warthog-ti-hardtail-29er/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Jonah’s Kokopelli post yesterday</a>, a few people emailed us asking what we thought about the cargo mounts on his fork lowers. Jonah has had them loaded up with bottles and cargo bags without issue. While there have been a number of similar products on the market, including the made in Durango <a href=\"http://www.kingcage.com/index.php?products=yes\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">USB from KingCage</a>, these Topeak mounts have proven to be a robust option as well and they won’t scratch your lowers as metal bands can. They install on tubes with ø20 – ø60mm diameters and are sold in pairs. Your local dealer can order these, so ask them if you’re interested.</p><p>See more at <a href=\"https://www.topeak.com/us/en/products/245-Accessories/1093-VERSAMOUNT\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Topeak</a>.</p></div><nav><h4>Related</h4></nav></article></section></div>","author":"prolly","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"f2a4ccd093c0a1595b6c775ae6ccb9fa3bfdf0e10484cda88d3f22a502505c77","category":"Cycling"}